just use scp. specify the file and then the machine

scp myfile.txt user@myremotemachine:\home\myuser\myfolder

if you to transfer right to home folder you can omit all the path and just leave the ':'

scp myfile.txt user@myremotemachine:


where the double dots ':' are necessary 
without the ':' NO transfer will be made 


after you run the command you will be asked for the remote machhine password and then a line with the total transfer time and speed will appear

done!





Copy all files from local to remote using scp.

scp * remoteuser@remoteserver:/remote/folder/

Copy all files and folders recursively from local to remote using scp.

scp -r * remoteuser@remoteserver:/remote/folder/